data.title: I was not impressed
data.text: I have heard good things about their cakes though. We tried an apple pie, twice in fact, and they were both the same. Crust seemed undercooked and doughy. Pricey too. We did not like the cookies either. I have not been back but tempted to try a cupcake when I'm in the area, as I've heard those were good.

data.title: Excellent French Maccaroons
data.text: We ordered multiple desserts for my daughters wedding and the owners gave us an excellent price and did not disappoint. We purchased a variety of maccaroons and mini cheesecakes and they were amazing!

data.title: Great bakery with unique goods
data.text: Very small bakery, yet had a nice selection of mouth watering goodies.  I bought a canoli and a coconut cream personal pie. Both were excellent.  The canoli was my favorite.  They also had chocolate covered strawberries and a host of very tempting goodies.  A little off the freeway, but WELL worth the visit.  I stopped here with a friend on our way to wine tasting.

data.title: Excellent special order!
data.text: I love cinnamon raisin rolls, and it's hard to find them.  I saw a note on Facebook from this establishment, and asked if they could make these for me.  They absolutely agreed.  I ordered a dozen.  Julie packed the frosting on the side so we could heat them up and then ice them.  It's only 3 days later, and they're gone.  And they were HUGE.  I'll definitely ask for these again!

data.title: Yummy new bakery in Murrieta
data.text:
This is a bakery, not a restaurant.  It's only been open a few months.  It's next door to Calhoun's Restaurant, and near Anthony's and The Mill restaurants.

The bakery has 2 cases full of all kinds of beautiful baked goods, including cakes, cookies, pastries, etc.  In addition, they sell yummy cheese spreads.  We tried the smoked salmon; it was sooooo tasty - this will be our new hostess gift.

They are closed on Sundays, so be sure to stock up.
